        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=9290&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=+&Topic_Title=Here+is+a+nice+quote+for+ya%2E%2E%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Spoke with GZ again here is the news:</P><P>Some of the Magician item summons are getting upgraded soon to make them more viable. <BR>As for Magician Pets - a lot of tests of Mage vs Necro pets have been run at Verant. The dev team feel that Mage pets are powerful enough. They won't ever be able to wield any form of weapon such as Magician summoned swords. In his words "That would push it a little too far". <BR>PC Enchanters will never be able to have both a summoned pet and charmed NPC. One of the dev teams groundrules for EQ was that no player would ever have two pets at the same time. <BR>GZ is going to look into the problem with Magician rain spells only giving what appears to be two rounds of damage. <BR>The Enchanter AC levels on the Shadow series are correct. No other Magi type gets "castable on others" AC spells. That the Enchanter does means that if you don't have a Cleric, you still get somebody who can buff your AC. The Enchanter is straying into the Cleric's area - the Cleric is better, but at least the Enchanter has the option <BR>I also put this to him about Wizards: Wizards don't really seem to be the ultimate damage dealers they should be. They just chew through the mana too fast for the damage they do. The other classes can do the equivalent damage with maybe a few hundred more mana spent all up. A lot of wizards feel that at high levels they don't have the pure blasting power they imagined a level 50 should have. <BR> <BR>His response: Wizards are the ultimate damage dealers for damage done in a short period of time. In this area, they have no rivals - hands down. Ice Comet cast twice does more damage in 13 seconds that most other casters can do in twice the amount of time. Is this useful in all situations? No. Does this mean that the Wizard class is uniquely qualified to save the party when the situation gets bad? Yes <BR>Keep in mind this comment on wizards is focusing on Level 49 and 50 Wizards. The fact that Ice Comet is unbeatable is all good and well, but with Plane of Fear now almost impossible I don't know how sustainable it is, since getting the spell is now a major hurdle.  <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P><BR>Just took that off the eqcasters site - news archive - fun to go back and look at the old posts...</P><P>Amazing what was said back then....</P><P></P><P>- CK</font></td>
      </tr>

